09/04/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The US Liaison Office in Pristina officially became the US Embassy in Kosovo on Tuesday (April 8th). US Ambassador in charge Tina Kaidanow said the move reflected Washington's dedication to the well-being of Kosovo and all its citizens. Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu added, "One part of the work for the establishment of diplomatic relations was crowned today, while the rest will be accomplished when a Kosovo Embassy opens in the US." Over 30 countries have recognised Kosovo's independence from Serbia. (Zeri, Koha Ditore, Express - 09/04/08; RTK - 08/04/08)
